{{Taxobox | image = | image_caption = | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Planctomycetes]] | classis = [[Phycisphaerae]] | subclassis = | ordo = [[Tepidisphaerales]] | subordo = | familia = [[Tepidisphaeraceae]] | genus = '''''Tepidisphaera''''' | genus_authority = Kovaleva et al. 2015<ref name=Tepidisphaera>{{cite journal |last1=Parte |first1=A.C. |title=Tepidisphaera |journal=www.bacterio.net |url=http://www.bacterio.net/tepidisphaera.html}}</ref> | type_species = ''Tepidisphaera mucosa''<ref name=Tepidisphaera/> | subdivision_ranks = [[Species]] | subdivision = ''[[Tepidisphaera mucosa|T. mucosa]]''<ref name=Tepidisphaera/> | synonyms = }}
'''''Tepidisphaera''''' is a genus of bacteria from the family of [[Planctomycetaceae]] with one known species (''[[Tepidisphaera mucosa]]'').<ref name=Tepidisphaera/><ref>{{cite journal |title=Tepidisphaera |journal=www.uniprot.org |url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/1771356 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Parker |first1=Charles Thomas |last2=Garrity |first2=George M |title=Taxonomic Abstract for the genera. |journal=The NamesforLife Abstracts |date=1 January 2003 |doi=10.1601/tx.26353 |language=en}}</ref> ''Tepidisphaera mucosa'' has been isolated from a [[hot spring]] from the [[Lake Baikal]] in [[Kamchatka]] in [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kovaleva |first1=OL |last2=Merkel |first2=AY |last3=Novikov |first3=AA |last4=Baslerov |first4=RV |last5=Toshchakov |first5=SV |last6=Bonch-Osmolovskaya |first6=EA |title=Tepidisphaera mucosa gen. nov., sp. nov., a moderately thermophilic member of the class Phycisphaerae in the phylum Planctomycetes, and proposal of a new family, Tepidisphaeraceae fam. nov., and a new order, Tepidisphaerales ord. nov. |journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology |date=February 2015 |volume=65 |issue=Pt 2 |pages=549–55 |doi=10.1099/ijs.0.070151-0 |pmid=25404483}}</ref>
