{{Infobox museum | name = Science Center Tietomaa | native_name = Tiedekeskus Tietomaa | native_name_lang = Finnish | image = Tietomaa Oulu 1989.jpg | imagesize = 200 | caption = Tietomaa in 1989. | alt = | map_type = | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|65|01|05|N|025|29|03|E|region:FI-14|display=inline,title}} | established = {{Start date|1988|06}}<ref name="Manninen">{{cite book |last=Manninen |first=Turo |year=1995 |title=Oulun kaupungin historia VI |language=Finnish |publisher= Oulun kaupunki |trans-title=History of the City of Oulu VI|pages=358–359 |isbn=951-9234-48-9}}</ref> | dissolved = | location = [[Myllytulli]], [[Oulu]] | type = Science Center | collection = | visitors = 74 567 (2008)<ref name="facts">{{cite web |url=http://www.tietomaa.fi/media/tietomaa-fakta |title=Faktat |language= Finnish |trans-title=Facts | publisher=Tietomaa |accessdate=19 June 2013 }}</ref> | director = Jonna-Marleena Härö<ref name="facts"/> | president = | curator = | owner = City of Oulu<ref name="facts"/> | publictransit = Local bus nr 17<ref name="busmap">{{cite web |url= http://kartta.ouka.fi/photos/joukkoliikenne2013_kesa_keskusta.pdf |title=Keskustan liikenne |year= 2013 |work= |publisher= City of Oulu |accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref> | car_park = | network = | website = [http://www.tietomaa.fi/index.php?id=1&lang_id=1 www.tietomaa.fi] }} '''Tietomaa''' is a science center in [[Oulu]], [[Finland]]. It is located in [[Myllytulli]] neighbourhood near the city centre. It is the first science centre in Finland and it was opened in June 1988.<ref name="Manninen"/>
Tietomaa is located in old buildings of the Veljekset Åström Oy, a former leather processing factory. The main exhibitions are located in the former power station. Tietomaa's {{convert|45|m|ft|adj=on}} observation tower with a glass elevator outside the tower is a former water tower of the factory.
